CRAVENSWORTH leaned inwardly at the start, tracked along the inside but faded. ROYAL AIR FORCE laid off of the pace in the four path, spun into the lane in the six path and tired.

FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of $24,600 At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since April 17 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $35,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One mile out of the chute.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORE THAN LOOKS broke inwardly, laid off of the pace in the three to four path, fanned to the six path entering the lane, rallied outside of foes while taking a bump from an inner rival inside the final furlong, yet sustained his charge in the closing stages to surge past the leader nearing the wire. FEARLESS SOLDIER set the pace along the inside, vied with an outer bidder around the far turn, held firm through midstretch, inched away entering the final sixteenth, but was caught by an outer on-charging foe in the closing stages. MIRANDA RIGHTS pursued from midpack along the inside, vacated the rail while vying with an outer DEMOLITION DUKE for show in upper stretch, drifted out and bumped that foe leaving the furlong grounds, yet sustained his grinding advance after getting outkicked by the eventual winner in the final sixteenth to re-gain show late. DEMOLITION DUKE tracked along the inside, tipped to take aim outside of the top pair straightening for home, but was herded outwardly by an inner rival entering the final furlong, took contact from that one passing that marker and transferred it to an outer foe in the process, then got outkicked and chased among foes. OCEAN POINTE stalked three wide, ranged up approaching the far turn, vied two wide around that bend, but failed to sustain even terms coming to midstretch, was turned away at the sixteenth pole and weakened late. ANGLOPHILE pursued from midpack two to three wide, spun for home in the five path, but shied from an inner rival while between horses at the furlong grounds and lacked a bid. THREE ON THE TREE was pinched between horses at the start, laid unhurried along the inside, then in the two path around the far turn before sustaining a rail chase through the lane, but lacked a bid. GO BALI GO leaned outwardly at the start, prompted along the inside early on, shifted two wide and outside of the pace setter around the first turn, crept closer along with an outer rival approaching the far turn, but got outmoved by that one entering that bend and yielded between horses turning for home. ROJA REDEMPTION trailed along the inside, failed to gain in the five path around the far turn and made little impact. POINT PROVEN raced at the rear two to three wide and was outrun turning for home. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REVIEWING THE STRETCH RUN, MIRANDA RIGHTS WAS DISQAULIFED AND PLACED FOURTH.

WET PAINT saved ground while patiently trailing the short field, continued on at the rear entering the lane, yet offered a rail rally in upper stretch to gain place from an outer rival leaving the furlong pole, then gradually narrowed the clear leader's margin in the late stages. FLAMAND bobbled slightly upon leaving the starting gate, was intently rated off of the leader to stalk from the inside under firm restraint, gained place in the two path turning for home as the leader kicked away, but lost that position to an inner rival at the furlong grounds before lasting for show. CHAMPAGNE CALLING laid off of the pace three wide, floated to the four path while chasing outside of rivals turning for home, then lacked a bid and was fended off for show through the final furlong. SABRA TUFF stalked two wide, but was urged in hopes of sustaining that position entering the far turn and weakened between horses leaving the quarter pole.
